  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Lord
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave this message to Jonah son of
        Amittai: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGet up and go to the great city of Nineveh. Announce my judgment
        against it because I have seen how wicked its people are.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Jonah got up and went in the opposite direction to get away from
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. He went down to the port of Joppa, where
        he found a ship leaving for Tarshish. He bought a ticket and went on board,
        hoping to escape from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> by sailing to Tarshish.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> hurled a powerful wind over the
        sea, causing a violent storm that threatened to break the ship apart. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Fearing for their lives, the desperate sailors shouted to their gods
        for help and threw the cargo overboard to lighten the ship.\n\tBut all this
        time Jonah was sound asleep down in the hold. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So the captain went down after him. \u201CHow can you sleep at a
        time like this?\u201D he shouted. \u201CGet up and pray to your god! Maybe
        he will pay attention to us and spare our lives.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the crew cast lots to see which of them had offended the gods
        and caused the terrible storm. When they did this, the lots identified Jonah
        as the culprit. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CWhy has this awful storm come down on us?\u201D they demanded.
        \u201CWho are you? What is your line of work? What country are you from?
        What is your nationality?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Jonah answered, \u201CI am a Hebrew, and I worship the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,
        the God of heaven, who made the sea and the land.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The sailors were terrified when they heard this, for he had already
        told them he was running away from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t. \u201COh,
        why did you do it?\u201D they groaned. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And since the storm was getting worse all the time, they asked him,
        \u201CWhat should we do to you to stop this storm?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CThrow me into the sea,\u201D Jonah said, \u201Cand it will
        become calm again. I know that this terrible storm is all my fault.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Instead, the sailors rowed even harder to get the ship to the land.
        But the stormy sea was too violent for them, and they couldn\u2019t make
        it. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then they cried out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, Jonah\u2019s
        God. \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t,\u201D they pleaded, \u201Cdon\u2019t
        make us die for this man\u2019s sin. And don\u2019t hold us responsible for
        his death. O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you have sent this storm upon
        him for your own good reasons.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then the sailors picked Jonah up and threw him into the raging sea,
        and the storm stopped at once! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The sailors were awestruck by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        great power, and they offered him a sacrifice and vowed to serve him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: '  [COMMENT[1]]Now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had arranged for
        a great fish to swallow Jonah. And Jonah was inside the fish for three days
        and three nights.'
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '1:17 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: Verse 1:17 is numbered 2:1 in Hebrew text.
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
  - verses:
    - title: "Jonah\u2019s Prayer"
      content: '  [COMMENT[1]]Then Jonah prayed to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        his God from inside the fish. '
      comments:
      - number: 
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
      - number: '2:1 '
        contents:
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
        - ft: Verses 2:1-10 are numbered 2:2-11 in Hebrew text.
          body: 
        - ft: '  '
          body: 
    - title: 
      content: "He said,\n\t\u201CI cried out to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in my great trouble,\n\tand he answered me.\n\tI called to you from the land
        of the dead,[COMMENT[0]]and <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you heard me!  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:2 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: from Sheol.
    - title: 
      content: "You threw me into the ocean depths,\n\tand I sank down to the heart
        of the sea.\n\tThe mighty waters engulfed me;\n\tI was buried beneath your
        wild and stormy waves.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then I said, \u2018O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t, you have driven
        me from your presence.\n\tYet I will look once more toward your holy Temple.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CI sank beneath the waves,\n\tand the waters closed over me.\n\tSeaweed
        wrapped itself around my head.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I sank down to the very roots of the mountains.\n\tI was imprisoned
        in the earth,\n\twhose gates lock shut forever.\n\tBut you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        my God,\n\tsnatched me from the jaws of death!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As my life was slipping away,\n\tI remembered the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t.\n\tAnd
        my earnest prayer went out to you\n\tin your holy Temple.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Those who worship false gods\n\tturn their backs on all God\u2019s
        mercies.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I will offer sacrifices to you with songs of praise,\n\tand I
        will fulfill all my vows.\n\tFor my salvation comes from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        alone.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> ordered the fish to spit Jonah
        out onto the beach.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Jonah Goes to Nineveh
      content: 'Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to Jonah a second time: '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "\u201CGet up and go to the great city of Nineveh, and deliver the
        message I have given you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "This time Jonah obeyed the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t\u2019s
        command and went to Nineveh, a city so large that it took three days to see
        it all.[COMMENT[0]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '3:3 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: "a great city to God, of three days\u2019 journey."
    - title: 
      content: "On the day Jonah entered the city, he shouted to the crowds: \u201CForty
        days from now Nineveh will be destroyed!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The people of Nineveh believed God\u2019s message, and from the greatest
        to the least, they declared a fast and put on burlap to show their sorrow.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When the king of Nineveh heard what Jonah was saying, he stepped
        down from his throne and took off his royal robes. He dressed himself in
        burlap and sat on a heap of ashes. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the king and his nobles sent this decree throughout the city:\n\t\u201CNo
        one, not even the animals from your herds and flocks, may eat or drink anything
        at all. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'People and animals alike must wear garments of mourning, and everyone
        must pray earnestly to God. They must turn from their evil ways and stop
        all their violence. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Who can tell? Perhaps even yet God will change his mind and hold
        back his fierce anger from destroying us.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: When God saw what they had done and how they had put a stop to their
        evil ways, he changed his mind and did not carry out the destruction he had
        threatened.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "\u2019s Mercy"
      content: 'This change of plans greatly upset Jonah, and he became very angry. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So he complained to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> about it: \u201CDidn\u2019t
        I say before I left home that you would do this, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t?
        That is why I ran away to Tarshish! I knew that you are a merciful and compassionate
        God, slow to get angry and filled with unfailing love. You are eager to turn
        back from destroying people. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Just kill me now, <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\n\t! I\u2019d rather
        be dead than alive if what I predicted will not happen.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> replied, \u201CIs it right for you
        to be angry about this?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then Jonah went out to the east side of the city and made a shelter
        to sit under as he waited to see what would happen to the city. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> God arranged for a leafy plant
        to grow there, and soon it spread its broad leaves over Jonah\u2019s head,
        shading him from the sun. This eased his discomfort, and Jonah was very grateful
        for the plant.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But God also arranged for a worm! The next morning at dawn the worm
        ate through the stem of the plant so that it withered away. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And as the sun grew hot, God arranged for a scorching east wind to
        blow on Jonah. The sun beat down on his head until he grew faint and wished
        to die. \u201CDeath is certainly better than living like this!\u201D he exclaimed.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then God said to Jonah, \u201CIs it right for you to be angry because
        the plant died?\u201D\n\t\u201CYes,\u201D Jonah retorted, \u201Ceven angry
        enough to die!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u201CYou feel sorry about
        the plant, though you did nothing to put it there. It came quickly and died
        quickly. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But Nineveh has more than 120,000 people living in spiritual darkness,[COMMENT[0]]
        not to mention all the animals. Shouldn\u2019t I feel sorry for such a great
        city?\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '4:11 '
        contents:
        - ft: 'Hebrew '
          body: "people who don\u2019t know their right hand from their left."
